        "id": 2048389,
        "name": "Don Cornutt",
        "username": "dcornutt",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/dcornutt/{size}/562_2.png",
        "created_at": "2016-11-05T22:16:18.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p><strong>1989 Roty Charmes-Chambertin TVV</strong></p>\n<p>Dark color.  The nose takes some coaxing.  Core of red fruit but some darker elements on the periphery.  Some element of forest floor.  A very young nose in many ways.  The palate is still quite structured but the fruit is absolutely penetrating in quality. There is only support from the tannin not bitterness or excessive grip.  Red core to the fruit.  A long finish that fans into a panoply of spice and earthy notes.  This is so young and SO very good!   A recent acquisition.  If I didn\u2019t know better, I would think I bought this from Bern\u2019s.  So youthful.  Amazing.  Years of life ahead.   <img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/2X/0/0ff9bfcdb0964982cd3240b6159868fbdf215b1a.gif\" width=\"24\" height=\"18\" alt=\"[cheers.gif]\" title=\"cheers\"></p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 9,
        "updated_at": "2022-06-02T20:06:57.668Z",
